Production at the German sports car manufacturer came to a temporary halt due to a major IT failure, Porsche confirmed to Xinhua on Wednesday. <img class="alignnone wp-image-650694" src="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/Porsche-1.gif?resize=392%2C221&#038;ssl=1" alt="IT failure temporarily shuts down production at Porsche" width="392" height="221" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/Porsche-1.gif?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/Porsche-1.gif?resize=58%2C33&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/Porsche-1.gif?resize=260%2C146&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/Porsche-1.gif?resize=200%2C113&amp;ssl=1 200w" sizes="(max-width: 392px) 100vw, 392px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> A Porsche spokesperson stressed that an internal problem was the reason for the failure, not an external cyber attack. A defective data storage unit triggered the problem while software that was supposed to contain the disruption also failed. The car manufacturing management had already informed all employees worldwide by e-mail about the IT failure on Tuesday. More than 200 servers at Porsche were shut down. All processes based on SAP software were affected. In the Porsche headquarters in Zuffenhausen in the north of Stuttgart, where for example the Taycan, Porsche’s first all-electric sports car, is manufactured, NAN reported. The IT failure caused a complete stop of the production line.One of its factory in Leipzig was also affected. In addition to the production, the IT failure also affected operations at Porsche’s spare parts warehouse as well as some customer services. ⤖Porsche’s unveils first fully electric sports car ⤖Manchester City star, Sergio Aguero involved in auto accident on way to training Production was restarted successively on Tuesday evening local time. “We have rebooted almost all systems”, a Porsche spokesperson told the German magazine Spiegel. “There will be no permanent economic damage and production will try to catch up quickly”, a spokesperson told Xinhua. Vanguard News Nigeria. IT is the archetypal sports car for everyday driving, and a style icon that is unmistakable as both the face and heart of the Porsche brand: the 911. Today in Zuffenhausen, the one-millionth model rolled off the production line – a Carrera S in a special “Irish Green” exterior colour,… May 12, 2017 In "Motoring" The year 2013 marks the anniversary of Porsche’s most iconic car: the 911. For the last 50 years this rear-engined model has been equally at home on the racetrack as on the road. Its genetic DNA can be found in every other Porsche model. With over 820,000 units built, the… March 9, 2013 In "Motoring" PORSCHE presented its first fully-electric sports car to the public with a spectacular world premiere held simultaneously on three continents. “The Taycan links our heritage to the future. It carries forward the success story of our brand - a brand that has fascinated and thrilled people the world over for… September 13, 2019 In "Motoring"